<br>
Just my 2 cents, I do not think Ponds was trying to make F&amp;F and Reso allies.&quot;<br>
<br>
Reso kiboshed any hopes of an &quot;alliance&quot; or profitable diplomacy in the near future with its collective actions.  The implication that FnF exacerbated the situation is inaccurate.<br>
<br>
&quot;I think she is just expressing how she feels, which is quite similiar to my feeelings. Which would be, we do not have to be best friends.&quot;<br>
<br>
She/he can express her opinion, Witherweaver can express his, as can others, and if anyone doesn't like anyone else's opinion they can a) live with it peacefully or b) argue against it - such is life.  As for being &quot;best friends&quot;, high end EQ is a competitive game and people will act accordingly.  The problem that has arisen is where certain people do not recognize the demarkation line between EQ and RL.<br>
<br>
&quot;Both guilds have some great people and some not great people. Would just be nice if we could come to some sort of unserstand..on both sides...of we don't flame you...you don't flame us. Agree to disagree and still respect each others opinions.&quot; <br>
<br>
If you recall, there was an issue with various FnF and Reso members being banned from the respective boards.  The bans were lifted with an informal agreement to keep the flames down.  Immediately after that FnF has experienced a number of blatant flames on our boards (without reasonable provocation) and furthermore threats of physical violence from a Reso member against FnF members (which continues to this day) with very poor handling of the situation by Reso leadership.  <br>
<br>
Again, the problem isn't just about uber guilds flaming one another (it's the equivalent to having fans for opposing football teams try to out pep-rally each other), the problem occurs when members/fans of one team cross the line.<br>
<br>
&quot;We can no more make all of our members conform then you can yours. But, I do not see where it hurts to step forward and say, &quot;I for one will not make this a personal war&quot;. Maybe if a few of us would do so, others would follow.&quot;<br>
<br>
That presumes that other people view these &quot;flame wars&quot; in the same manner that you do.  Namely that they mean more outside of the game than they do - which is a view of yours that many of us don't subscribe to. <br>
<br>
&quot;I commend Ponds on her post.&quot;<br>
